snippet.textDisplay: How can y'all have so many good cars available for 500£? Here in the States if your budget is $500 all you'll find is a bunch of busted ass old Buicks, rusted Civics (hopefully they run), and crap like Ford Focus sedans with 280k miles that burn more oil than gas. Maybe I'm looking in the wrong places, but that's always been my experience. You'll NEVER find a modified Miata (MX5) for less than $1000 that has an engine and transmission still in it.
snippet.textOriginal: How can y'all have so many good cars available for 500£? Here in the States if your budget is $500 all you'll find is a bunch of busted ass old Buicks, rusted Civics (hopefully they run), and crap like Ford Focus sedans with 280k miles that burn more oil than gas.
